attachmentHtml:
PC Number: 2012-1026

Date: 2012-08-20

His Excellency the Governor General in Council, on the recommendation of the Minister of Indian Affairs and Northern Development and in accordance with the Settlement Agreement dated September 14, 1995, sets apart for the joint use and benefit of the Carry the Kettle Band, Cote Band, Cowessess Band, Day Star Band, Fishing Lake Band, Gamblers Band, Gordon Band, Kahkewistahaw Band, Kawacatoose Band, Keeseekoose Band, Key Band, Kinistin Band, Little Black Bear Band, Muscowpetung Band, Muskowekwan Band, Nekaneet Band, Ocean Man Band, Ochapowace Band, Okanese Band, Pasqua Band, Peepeekisis Band, Pheasant Rump Band, Piapot Band, Pine Creek Band, Rolling River Band, Sakimay Band, Sapotaweyak Band, Star Blanket Band, Tootinawazeebeeng Band, Waywayseecappo Band, White Bear Band, Wuskwi Sipihk Band and Yellow Quill Band as an addition to Treaty Four Reserve Grounds No. 77, in Saskatchewan, the land described in the attached schedule, consisting of 0.800 hectares (1.98 acres), excluding mines and minerals.


Sur recommandation du ministre des Affaires indiennes et du Nord canadien et conformément à l’accord intitulé Settlement Agreement daté du 14 septembre 1995, Son Excellence le Gouverneur général en conseil met de côté à l’usage et au profit conjoints des bandes suivantes: bande Carry the Kettle, bande Cote, bande Cowessess, bande Day Star, bande Fishing Lake, bande Gamblers, bande Gordon, bande Kahkewistahaw, bande Kawacatoose, bande Keeseekoose, bande Key, bande Kinistin, bande Little Black Bear, bande Muscowpetung, bande Muskowekwan, bande Nekaneet, bande Ocean Man, bande Ochapowace, bande Okanese, bande Pasqua, bande Peepeekisis, bande Pheasant Rump, bande Piapot, bande Pine Creek, bande Rolling River, bande Sakimay, bande Sapotaweyak, bande Star Blanket, bande Tootinawazeebeeng, bande Waywayseecappo, bande White Bear, bande Wuskwi Sipihk et bande Yellow Quill, à titre d’ajout à la réserve Treaty Four Reserve Grounds No. 77, en Saskatchewan, les terres délimitées à l’annexe ci-jointe, lesquelles sont constituées de 0,800 hectare (1,98 acres), mines et minéraux exclus.
